  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A prospective observation study to screen adult obese (BMI ≥30 kg/m2) patients who were newly
      admitted to the medical intensive care units and turned out to be diagnosed as Obesity
      hypoventilation syndrome(OHS). The investigators purpose is to look into the prevalence,
      predictive factors, and outcomes of OHS in these critically ill patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
